All in all, this sequel is fantastic due to the production, the settings, story, special effects and of course, cool cars. Thumbs up.

Title: The Fate of the Furious - Official Trailer - #F8 In Theaters April 14 (HD)
Comment:
People should stop hating on the new fast and furious movies just because Paul isn't here with us.  I mean, I loved Paul Walker.  I idolized him and I still do.  When he passed, it was like losing a family member.  All of my friends started getting angry that Fast and Furious movies will suck because Paul is not here, but that is just because people are jumping on the bandwagon.  The producers of F&F can't just bring Paul back, even though it would make all of the world's problems end if they did.  But instead of hating on this series, we should appreciate how far it has come, and not hate on the fact that the movies aren't completely street-racing based anymore.  We should come together as a community of F&F watchers, and appreciate the good things about these movies.


 R.I.P Paul.  Miss you a lot bro. :(

They took a terrible turn with the fifth movie. It looks like they picked the worst movie so far in the series - the second - and said: hey let's do this again, but without the car tuning scene stuff. While not being a total letdown it didn't felt like a F&F movie at all. But instead of going back to the roots they are just riding the same horse over and over again. Each and every F&F movie since then seems to be like the fifth but its get stupider with each instalment. The sixth was almost unbearably stupid. I watched the 7th only because I wanted to see how they deal with Pauls death. I wish I didn't. Unless some wonder happens I'll pass on the 8th and all the crap that's probably about to come with the F&F label.

Comment: Dom is the bloodline of the family - he is literally behind it all and for that, we love him as a character. I know it seems brilliant to make him turn on his family as it will add for HUGE suspense and a plot twist, but honestly there is too strong of an attraction to the fans and Don that makes this franchise great. His connection to the Fast and Furious family is what made this series so unique and appreciable. Now, Dom turning on his family (even if he comes back to them) completely defeats the purpose of the series and contradicts what the fans love completely. I miss the old Fast and Furious where they would drive Tuners, race and do jobs because they loved it. Now, there's always SOMETHING that comes in the way. There is something that ALWAYS interferes. Don't get me wrong, I still like Fast 7 and 6, and I will probably enjoy this one nonetheless, but my heart will always be with the original five Fast and Furious movies (Fast Five was my favourite). Does anyone else agree?

Not gonna lie. When I first saw the title and thumb nail, I was thinking this was going to be one big ripoff. But as the trailer started playing out, I began to get excited. I think I enjoyed the trailer because of the simple fact that I got to see majority of characters I grew up with again. Tyrese is by far my favorite and I love the Rock's dry humor. 

Aside from the overuse of explosions in a TRAILER, I'm looking forward to this. I also love the Dom twist despite how 'cliche' and 'played out' it is. Face it, if any other character had turned we would find a way to justify it but with Dom everyone is asking "Why Dom when he preaches faithfully about family?" Maybe the plot is obvious, maybe it's not. Either way, spend the money to see or don't.

First scene - a car goes through the wall totally unscathed (today's Dodge Challenger is mostly plastic). I stopped the video. My God, I'm already disgusted. Someone kick me in the face, because I could be only overreacting.
Edit: ok, I pushed the play button. Again, today's Dodge Challenger pushes military Range Rover away - completely unscathed. How am I supposed to even trust the director? Am I an idiot or something? Does my intelligence really need to be treated like I was a mental hospital patient?
The trailer is 9/10, though. I really like the idea for the new movie, yet it's too much of a scripted-shootout one. It's good for New Years Eve and all those fireworks, but not for... Easter. ;)
Oh, and by the way - I think I just watched a whole movie here. It's only my feeling, though. And it is horrible. Like I didn't have to watch the shit in a theatre or something.
Come on, F. Gary Gray! What are you doing? Okay, it's an awesome movie, but come on! What the shit? Why are you making the plot so simple? Do not ever let that scripter write for you again. Why am I sayin' that? Because this should be about cars, not shooting and James-Bond-kinda'-shit. Simple as that. Really... Easy as that.
One last thing - how could you NOT choose the Supra instead of the Murcielago? The answer for this will never ever be found.

Title: The Fate of the Furious - Official Trailer - #F8 In Theaters April 14 (HD)
Comment:
Legit garbage. Let's be honest here: The only reason anyone would want to see this, is to prove that they were right about how he'll really turn out to be a good person, but was pretending to be bad all along to get that Charlize's character out of the way. Other than that, why would anyone wanna see this movie? They really should have ended it with the last one. That movie ended in a way which imo, was a good farewell to all the characters that are still alive, along with the series as a whole. 

Then, we're told they're making another one which at first sounded awesome and cool, but by looking at this trailer, it's clear they've ran out of ideas and legit had to make Dom the bad guy to keep the story going? It sure the hell wasn't because it sounded like a great idea on paper. There were so many ways they could have gone with this, and they picked such a cheap and unoriginal idea to make yet another movie of the series. 

But, sadly enough, this movie will sell well because it's a series that everyone loves (including me). Just don't like where they've went with this one. But I'm sure we'll have a better idea, or not, of why they picked this route for when it comes out next year.

Comment: As an action film and sequel to the seventh film this looks pretty awesome. I have to admit i didn't join the fan base til Furious 7. These films were sort of off my radar as i'm not really a racing enthusiast. I didn't really engage with the franchise til a friend of mine dragged me to the cinema in 2014 and on an action movie, humor and emotional level I enjoyed that very much and then i went back and watched the first 6 and really enjoyed those too. That's probably why I'm not too concerned with the less street racing more action approach. In terms of an exciting and unpredictable place of taking the franchise this looks good to me. Even if they are mainly vehicular mayhem and action nowadays, you gotta admit that they do what they do spectacularly and to still keep the emotional core of the family center stage that's impressive for an action franchise for it to have that much on it's mind. Hell I'll watch it, just for the action but the drama looks pretty intense too. Glad Mr Nobody and Statham are back, they were cool in 7.

Comment:
The way I see it there are only 3 possible outcomes for this movies based off the trailer
1) Charlize Theron has Dom under some sort of chip or brain manipulation, hence Kurt Russell saying "she's the best form of cyber terrorism" and this would be kinda dumb and silly
2) Theron has threatened Brian and Mia and she is using dom for a job,  plot hole here is there is no way this would happen without brain getting involved,  and only way they could do that is thru cgi and I don't see them doing that 
Which only leaves option 3 which seems most likely.
3) Theron kills Brian and threatens Mia and the rest of the crew if he doesn't work with her. This is the only explanation as to why Brian wouldn't come in and take dom down himself. Obviously this would be borderline disrespectful and would probably piss off a lot of fans. 
Either way, as a long time fan I'm kinda worried about this one. Something tells me it gonna finally cross that fine line it's been walking between a cool movie and a silly movie.  I hope they prove me wrong.
